    "body": "I just copied it over from itlikelike, I wasn't aware it wasn't a \"Standard\" thing we did. I used it and it mostly helped, especially in cases where there's no between-var for it (like `GET_ATTRS(ip)->0x4` vs `((itBombHeiAttributes*) ip->xC4_article_data->x4_specialAttributes)->0x4`). I did have to break it a few times for permuter reasons to get 100% (like break out article data for example), but I'd say it makes the code more readable / helps personally",
